<title>USA: Hills Stores stake cut by FMR group.</title>
<headline>Hills Stores stake cut by FMR group.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-03-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>A group led by FMR Corp said Monday it cut its stake in Hills Stores Co to 511,337 common shares or 4.99 percent from 5.12 percent.</p>
<p>In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the group said its latest transactions include the sale of 12,800 common shares between March 12 and March 17 at prices ranging from $4.250 to $4.625 per share.</p>
<p>FMR Corp is the parent to Fidelity Management &amp; Research Co, investment adviser to Fidelity Funds.</p>
<p>Hills, based in Canton, Mass., operates discount department stores.</p>
